public class StackToTrail<E>
extends java.util.Stack<E>

The StackToTrail extends the java.util.Stack. Is overrides the functionality for push and pop. In general, it will invoke the super method whenever the methods push() and pop() are invoked. If it is not set to restoring mode, it will also add information to the trail of the current ChoicePoint.

The trail can be used to track back to a former state of the execution. Hence, when pushing an item the command to pop will be added to the trail, and when popping an item the command to push it will be added to the trail.
